data.enText: a large tree with spreading branches, that produces smooth brown nuts inside cases which are covered with spikes . There are several types of chestnut tree.
a smooth brown nut of a chestnut tree, some types of which can be eaten
a horse of a reddish-brown colour

data.chText: 陈腐的笑话；老掉牙的故事
data.enText: an old joke or story that has been told so many times that it is no longer amusing or interesting

tr: a dark golden-brown or reddish-brown horse
a small horny callus on the inner surface of a horse's leg
edible nut of any of various chestnut trees of the genus Castanea
any of several attractive deciduous trees yellow-brown in autumn
yield a hard wood and edible nuts in a prickly bur
wood of any of various chestnut trees of the genus Castanea
(of hair or feathers) of a golden brown to reddish brown color

value.def: A chestnut or chestnut tree is a tall tree with broad leaves.
Chestnuts are the reddish-brown nuts that grow on chestnut trees. You can eat chestnuts.
Something that is chestnut is dark reddish-brown in colour.
If you refer to a statement, a story, or a joke as an old chestnut or a hoary chestnut, you mean that it has been repeated so often that it is no longer interesting.

example.ex: ...that old chestnut, the war between man and machines.
example.tran: 又是老掉牙的故事：人机大战

value.tran: 老掉牙的话(或故事、笑话);老一套
